passages.text: China (PRC) | Semiconductors
2Q25 Mixed; China Auto Market and Datacom as Focused Areas

2Q25 rev beat, but profitability was impacted by the remaining contribution from ODM business which had not yet closed, and mgt expected to reverse losses in Q3-4 estimated ar Rmb200-400m. China auto rev grew >40% YoY with accelerating new product R&D and launch and penetration in new customers. Datacom as another key area to develop, and Wingtech is now actively sending new samples to ODM/power supply vendor. Maintain BUY.

**2Q25 rev beat; Profitability disrupted by selling ODM arm.** Wingtech's 2Q25 rev dropped 29% YoY to Rmb12,242m, beating JFE/cons by 21%/40% mainly driven by demand recovery on semi segment and the remaining contribution from ODM business which had not yet closed.As a result of still containing ODM business on PnL with low GM (1.2% in Q2), overall GM rose 3.8ppt but declined 0.4ppt to 13.5%, missing JFE/cons by 3.5ppt/9.3ppt, and EBIT/NP were also below expected as Wingtech still needed to bear some transitional gains/losses from the deal. Given the local assets of ODM were settled on Jul 2 and oversea assets will also be settled soon, mgt expected to reverse the corresponding losses in Q3-4 on PnL, which was estimated to be Rmb200-400m.

**Active expanding to more clients especially in China; Datacom another growth curve.** Mgt pointed out in 2Q25, semi rev in China market saw >20% rev growth with robust performance across many downstream markets especially auto, industrial and consumer. Specifically, auto rev in China grew >40% YoY. As a leading international power/analog semi player, Wingtech has been accelerating new product R&D and launch. The latest gen of MOS products are manufactured in Lingang 12-inch fab with significant improvements in performance and cost,which have successfully obtained design winds of leading domestic EV customers and are expected to start mass production and shipment from Oct. Mgt also indicated it has secured orders for SiC MOS and IGBT products from domestic EV customers as well with deliveries expected to begin in 2H25, and its HV GaN products have already been adopted by multiple OEMs including Geely and Renault. In addition, datacom is another key area to develop. Mgt suggested its power/analog products have been widely adopted in AI server and data center,and is now actively sending new samples to ODM and power supply vendors, which could potentially become another important growth curve in coming years.

**Maintain BUY.** We put our NP forecasts in 2025E-27E by 10% to factor in the last impact before the settlement of selling ODM arm, which is still 7% above cons. Although forgoing ODM business theoretically means a lower ceiling for the company's size in long-term, by focusing its resources more efficiently on semi going forward, we think Wingtech has opportunity to deliver better than expected profit which still depends on mgt's execution ability. We maintain BUY with uCIF-based PT of Rmb49.80 (WACC 10.0%, terminal growth rate 5.3%), which implies 33%/21x 2025E/26E P/E and suggests 15% potential upside.
Equity ResearchAugust 31,2025

Investment Thesis / Where We Differ- Capacity ramp- up in Shanghai Lingang and overseas fabs, especially for IGBT and 3rd- Gen semi products- Market share gain in traditional power semi markets, especially auto products, which still face supply tightness- Non- smartphone ODM TAM growth and market share gain in tablet, notebook (especially from customer- A), wearable, server and IoT- Expansion of assembly orders to more product types from specific customers- Reloading camera module business with share gain among Android smartphone brands and further penetration from single/dual to triple cameras
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

Base Case, CNY49.8,+15% - Semiconductor shipments rise from 109bn in 2024 to 167bn/225bn in 2027E/30E - ODM smartphone shipments decrease from 106m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30E - Other ODM product shipments decrease from 43m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30 E - Camera module shipment decrease from 8m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30E - Price target of Rmb49.80 is based on end- 2025 DCF, with a WACC of \(10.0\%\) and a terminal growth rate of \(5.3\%\) (2030)

Upside Scenario, CNY56.78,+31% - Semiconductor shipments rise from 109bn in 2024 to 182bn/245bn in 2027E/30E - ODM smartphone shipments decrease from 106m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30E - Other ODM product shipments decrease from 43m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30 E - Camera module shipment decrease from 8m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30E - Price target of Rmb56.78 is based on end- 2025 DCF, with a WACC of \(10.0\%\) and a terminal growth rate of \(5.5\%\) (2030)

Downside Scenario, CNY31.3,- 28% - Semiconductor shipments rise from 109bn in 2024 to 137bn/185bn in 2027E/30E - ODM smartphone shipments decrease from 106m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30E - Other ODM product shipments decrease from 43m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30 E - Camera module shipment decrease from 8m in 2024 to 0m/0m in 2027E/30E - Price target of Rmb31.30 is based on end- 2025 DCF, with a WACC of \(10.0\%\) and a terminal growth rate of \(3.5\%\) (2030)

Sustainability MattersTop Material Issues:- Nexperia, as a Dutch competitor, may incur higher costs to manage and talent loss could occur, given delicate international relations, which increase the geopolitical risk to Wingtech's semiconductor business- Structural weakness in consumer electronics demand could reduce its production efficiency

Key ESG Targets:- By 2030 reduce the GHG emission density by \(30\%\) of product integration segment vs 2015, by more than \(20\%\) of semiconductor segment vs 2017, and by \(30\%\) of optical imaging segment vs 2016- Reduce water consumption of product integration segment by \(2\%\) each year- Nexperia plans to gradually stop the use of NMP (N-Methyl- 2-pyrrolidone) by 2025

Key Questions for Mgt:- What is the proportion of foreign customers of Nexperia and how do you deal with the potential geopolitical risk that could cause customer loss and talent loss?- How do you manage to maximize the synergistic effect among the three business segments? ESG Report: http://static.cninfo.com.cn/finalpage/2022- 06- 18/1213741434. PDF

Catalysts- Overall EV penetration on track- Continued supply tightness in auto semi components- Better-than- expected ramp- up and design wins in IGBT/SiC/GaN- Further market share gain in non- smartphone ODM products- Further market share gain in camera module- Potential favorable acquisition for business expansion.

WingtechWingtech is originally engaged in the research, development and manufacture of mobile terminals and smart hardware products. It conducts semiconductor business through subsidiary Nexperia, with products including bipolar transistors, diodes, MOSFET and logic devices.

Our price target for Wingtech of Rmb49.80 is based on end- 2025 DCF, with a WACC of \(10.0\%\) and a terminal growth rate of \(5.3\%\) (2030). Key risks include: 1) further downside to power semi ASP due to weak downstream demand; 2) fiercer competition in IGBT market; 3) slower- than- expected demand recovery in consumer electronics; 4) further downside to camera module demand; 5) impairment risk on goodwill; and 6) escalating geopolitical tension adds risks to the supply chain.
